<!-- Financial Brief Text Section #2 -->
<div class="section white">
  <div class="row container">
    <h2 class="header center">Breaking it down money-wise</h2>
    <p class="grey-text text-darken-3 lighten-3">Alright, lets assume you are earning a modest $3000 per month. And you save a healthy chunk of 20% from paycheck, the table below shows the annual saving and awards you get back!</p>

    <br>

    <%= render 'homepage/calculation' %>

    <br>

    <p>At the end of the year you will be getting back <%= number_to_currency(@twelve_percent_of_savings, precision: 0) %> worth of stuff just for saving <%= number_to_currency(@annual_savings /12, precision: 0) %> per month for 1 year. Now thats a pretty decent deal, you're happy and so is Hamlet. <i class="em em-pig"></i></p>
    <p>Out of the <%= number_to_currency(@annual_savings, precision: 0) %>, you get <%= number_to_currency(@twelve_percent_of_savings * 0.3, precision: 0) %> in cash and <%= number_to_currency(@twelve_percent_of_savings * 0.7, precision: 0) %> worth of Cache rewards! These rewards ranges from discounts at eateries or at boutiques.</p>
    <div class='row center-align'>
      <%= link_to('Financial Forecast', publicanalysis_path, :method => :get, class: "waves-effect waves-light btn") %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

